{
  "texts": [
    "With this approach, models are built with dropout layers enabled during both training and inference.",
    "During inference, a single image undergoes multiple forward passes in the network, with the resulting distribution representing the final prediction (mean) and uncertainty (standard deviation).",
    "Tile-level uncertainty can be translated into slide-level uncertainty and used for subsequent confidence thresholding, using our previously described uncertainty thresholding algorithm [31].",
    "Briefly, from a given set of validation predictions, an optimal uncertainty threshold is determined, below which predictions are more likely to be correct compared to predictions with higher uncertainty.",
    "Predictions with uncertainty above this threshold are then discarded."
  ]
}